<title>UK: Hyder says sells three hotels to Virgin.</title>
<headline>Hyder says sells three hotels to Virgin.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Britain's Hyder Plc said on Friday it had sold three of its hotels to the Virgin Hotels Group for 5.3 million stg.</p>
<p>The hotels -- Cwrt Bleddyn Hotel near Usk, Coed y Mwstr Hotel near Bridgend and Seiont Manor Hotel near Caernarvon -- were being operated by Virgin under a management contract since April 1994.</p>
<p>Hyder said the disposals were part of its programme to get out of its non-core activities.</p>
